This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with the automated detection of hip fractures from x-rays. It also involves the use of deep learning techniques, which makes it likely to be classified under the Machine Learning (cs.LG, cs.DL) categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the potential impact of the system on patient outcomes, which suggests a focus on Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of large amounts of medical data, which could also make it relevant to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) category.
